(23, '2746', '2024-10-18', '9.30AM-5.30PM', 'Learning, practicing, and brainstorming for a new project.', 'Learning:\r\n-Reviewed foundational concepts of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.\r\n-Learned how to structure HTML elements and style them using CSS.\r\n-Explored basic JavaScript syntax like variables, loops, and functions.\r\n\r\nPractice:\r\n-Created a simple web page using HTML and CSS that includes a header, footer, and a responsive navigation bar.\r\n-Implemented basic interactivity using JavaScript, such as toggling the navigation menu.\r\n\r\nBrainstorming:\r\n-Planned how to structure a static website layout for the project, considering various HTML tags and CSS styling approaches.\r\n-Identified key JavaScript functions needed for interactivity (e.g., form validation, event handling).', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(24, '2758', '2024-10-19', '9.30AM-5.30PM', 'My Tastk Registration_From using html ,css and basic javascript', 'Explanation:\r\nHTML Structure: The document includes a head section with metadata and styles, and a body section containing the registration form.\r\n\r\nForm Elements:\r\n\r\nCategory Name: A text input for the user to enter the name of the category.\r\nDescription: A text input for a brief description of the category.\r\nPriority Level: A dropdown select for choosing the priority level of the task category.\r\nStyling: Basic CSS is used to style the form, making it user-friendly and visually appealing.\r\n\r\nForm Submission: The form is set to submit data to the /submit endpoint via POST. You would need to handle this on the server side.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
