(875, '4194', '2025-10-16', '9AM-11AM', 'JavaScript Arrays Implementation', 'Implemented and practiced various JavaScript array methods to strengthen understanding of data manipulation and iteration.\r\nCovered important methods such as:\r\n\r\npush(), pop(), shift(), unshift() â for adding/removing elements.\r\n\r\nmap(), filter(), reduce(), forEach() â for transformation and iteration.\r\n\r\nindexOf(), includes(), slice(), splice(), concat() â for searching and modifying arrays.\r\n\r\nWorked on small programs that demonstrated how arrays handle dynamic data efficiently and how these methods simplify complex operations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(876, '4194', '2025-10-16', '11AM-1PM', 'JavaScript Concepts â Functions and Methods', 'Studied in-depth about functions in JavaScript and understood how they are the building blocks of code reusability.\r\nCovered topics like:\r\n\r\nFunction declaration and expression\r\n\r\nArrow functions (=>)\r\n\r\nFunction parameters and return values\r\n\r\nScope and Hoisting\r\n\r\nExplored methods â functions associated with objects â and practiced creating custom methods to perform specific operations.\r\nCompleted multiple exercises to understand how functions and methods can be combined to make modular and reusable code.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(877, '4194', '2025-10-16', '2PM-4PM', 'Introduction to DOM (Document Object Model)', 'Began studying the Document Object Model (DOM) â the programming interface for web documents.\r\nLearned about:\r\n\r\nThe structure of the DOM tree (nodes, elements, attributes, text).\r\n\r\nAccessing and modifying HTML elements using JavaScript (getElementById, querySelector, etc.).\r\n\r\nThe concept of events and event listeners for making interactive web pages.\r\n\r\nImplemented basic DOM manipulation examples to dynamically change content and styles through JavaScript.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(878, '4194', '2025-10-16', '4PM-6PM', 'DOM Practice and Integration', 'Continued hands-on practice on DOM operations, integrating array and function concepts with DOM manipulation.\r\nCreated small interactive programs, such as dynamically displaying array data on a webpage, updating content through user input, and changing CSS properties via script.\r\n\r\nThis session helped solidify understanding of how JavaScript interacts with the browser to create dynamic, user-friendly interfaces.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
