(921, '4194', '2025-10-21', '9AM-11AM', 'JavaScript â DOM (Document Object Model)', 'Studied the structure of the DOM and how HTML elements are represented as nodes and objects.\r\n\r\nLearned to access elements using JavaScript methods like:\r\n\r\ngetElementById()\r\n\r\ngetElementsByClassName()\r\n\r\ngetElementsByTagName()\r\n\r\nquerySelector() and querySelectorAll()\r\n\r\nUnderstood the tree-like hierarchy of the DOM and how JavaScript can read, update, and delete HTML elements dynamically.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(922, '4194', '2025-10-21', '11AM-1PM', 'JavaScript â DOM Manipulation', 'Practiced manipulating HTML elements dynamically using JavaScript.\r\n\r\nUpdated content with .innerText, .innerHTML, .textContent.\r\n\r\nChanged CSS styles dynamically using .style property.\r\n\r\nCreated and removed elements using createElement(), append(), and remove().', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(923, '4194', '2025-10-21', '2PM-4PM', 'JavaScript â Events', 'Learned about event handling in JavaScript.\r\n\r\nStudied different types of events such as click, mouseover, keyup, and change.\r\n\r\nImplemented event listeners using both inline events and addEventListener().\r\n\r\nUnderstood the concept of event bubbling and capturing.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(924, '4194', '2025-10-21', '4PM-6PM', 'JavaScript â Classes and Objects', 'Revised the concept of Objects in JavaScript (key-value pairs).\r\n\r\nCreated objects using object literals and constructors.\r\n\r\nLearned about ES6 Classes â how to define, create objects, and use constructors and methods.\r\n\r\nPracticed the use of this keyword and object-oriented principles like encapsulation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(925, '4196', '2025-10-22', '9AM-11AM', 'Home Page â Navbar & Logo (Hitz Crafty Website)', 'In this time Planned the home page structure and layout for the navigation bar and overall design placement.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(926, '4196', '2025-10-22', '11AM-1PM', 'Home Page â Navbar & Logo (Hitz Crafty Website)', 'Created a responsive Navbar using Bootstrap CSS with links like Home, Products, About, and Contact.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(927, '3697', '2025-10-22', '9AM-11AM', 'Database Configuration', 'Worked on configuring JDBC connection with MySQL database. Practiced loading the MySQL JDBC driver, establishing a database connection, and verifying successful connectivity using Java.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yandra Ravi Babu'),
(928, '3697', '2025-10-22', '11AM-1PM', 'CRUD Operations using JDBC', 'Implemented Insert, Update, Delete, and Retrieve operations using PreparedStatement in JDBC. Tested queries with the MySQL database and verified data manipulation through the console output.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yandra Ravi Babu'),
(929, '3697', '2025-10-22', '2PM-4PM', 'Debugging and Testing', 'Tested the JDBCâMySQL connectivity and resolved issues related to database configuration and SQL query execution. Verified successful interaction between the Java application and MySQL database through multiple test cases.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yandra Ravi Babu'),
(930, '4196', '2025-10-22', '2PM-4PM', 'Home Page â Navbar & Logo (Hitz Crafty Website)', 'Added the Hitz Crafty logo and brand name in the Navbar using Thymeleaf for dynamic rendering', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(931, '4194', '2025-10-22', '9AM-11AM', 'JavaScript â DOM Concepts', 'Learned the Document Object Model (DOM) and its importance in connecting HTML and JavaScript.\r\n\r\nUnderstood how the browser represents web pages as a tree of objects.\r\n\r\nStudied nodes, elements, attributes, and text content in the DOM hierarchy.\r\n\r\nExplored ways to access and modify elements using DOM methods like:\r\n\r\ndocument.getElementById()\r\n\r\ndocument.getElementsByClassName()\r\n\r\ndocument.querySelector() and document.querySelectorAll()', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(932, '4194', '2025-10-22', '11AM-1PM', 'JavaScript â DOM Properties', 'Practiced using various DOM properties to manipulate web elements dynamically.\r\n\r\nLearned about:\r\n\r\n.innerText, .innerHTML, and .textContent\r\n\r\n.style for inline styling\r\n\r\n.classList for adding/removing/toggling CSS classes\r\n\r\nModified HTML content and styles using JavaScript to make pages more interactive.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(933, '4194', '2025-10-22', '2PM-4PM', 'JavaScript â Events', 'Learned about events in JavaScript such as click, mouseover, keydown, and submit.\r\n\r\nUnderstood how JavaScript detects and responds to user interactions.\r\n\r\nImplemented basic event examples using both inline event attributes and event listeners.\r\n\r\nObserved how different event types behave on various HTML elements.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(934, '4194', '2025-10-22', '4PM-6PM', 'JavaScript â Event Handling Implementation', 'Practically implemented event handling using addEventListener() for cleaner and more flexible code.\r\n\r\nStudied the difference between inline events and external event listeners.\r\n\r\nLearned about event object, event bubbling, and event propagation.\r\n\r\nBuilt a small demo to show how multiple events can be handled on different elements.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
