(951, '4196', '2025-10-23', '4PM-6PM', 'Product Cards & Images Section (Hitz Crafty Website)', 'In the final session, I will apply advanced CSS styling and hover effects to enhance the visual appeal of the product cards. Iâll add features like smooth transitions, shadow effects, and color changes on hover to create a more interactive and professional-looking user interface. Additionally, Iâll review the overall responsiveness and make sure the product section looks consistent across different screen sizes and browsers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(952, '4194', '2025-10-23', '9AM-11AM', 'HTML & CSS Structure', 'Designed the Tic-Tac-Toe game layout using HTML.\r\n\r\nCreated a 9-box grid representing the game board using <button> elements.\r\n\r\nStyled the game interface with CSS:\r\n\r\nUsed flexbox to center and align the game grid.\r\n\r\nAdded background colors, borders, box shadows, and hover effects for better UI.\r\n\r\nDesigned buttons for Reset Game and New Game.\r\n\r\nLearned how to structure a responsive game board using viewport units (vmin, vh) for dynamic sizing.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(953, '4194', '2025-10-23', '11AM-1PM', 'JavaScript â Game Logic Setup', 'Selected HTML elements using querySelector and querySelectorAll.\r\n\r\nInitialized game variables:\r\n\r\nturnO to track current player (O or X).\r\n\r\ncount to track number of moves for detecting a draw.\r\n\r\nDefined winning patterns as arrays to check all possible win combinations.\r\n\r\nImplemented reset and new game functions to restart the game and clear the board.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(954, '4194', '2025-10-23', '2PM-4PM', 'JavaScript â Player Interaction', 'Added click event listeners for each box to allow players to mark O or X.\r\n\r\nImplemented logic to alternate turns between player O and player X.\r\n\r\nDisabled clicked boxes to prevent overwriting moves.\r\n\r\nUpdated move counter (count) to track total moves and detect draw situations.\r\n\r\nPracticed conditional statements to handle turn changes and check for draw conditions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(955, '4194', '2025-10-23', '4PM-6PM', 'JavaScript â Win/Draw Detection & UI Updates', 'Implemented checkWinner() function to evaluate all winning patterns.\r\n\r\nCreated showWinner() function to display winner message dynamically using DOM manipulation.\r\n\r\nImplemented gameDraw() function to show draw message when all boxes are filled without a winner.\r\n\r\nPracticed DOM manipulation by updating text, showing/hiding message containers, and enabling/disabling boxes.\r\n\r\nConnected Reset Game and New Game buttons with the reset functionality.\r\n\r\nLearned how to integrate HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to make an interactive game.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(956, '2789', '2025-10-23', '9AM-11AM', 'Project and training department ', 'Working on personal project', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2789'),
(957, '2789', '2025-10-23', '11AM-1PM', 'Project and training department ', 'today java training session is done at 1.00pm by newton ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2789'),
(958, '4196', '2025-10-24', '9AM-11AM', 'Tic Tac Toe Game Development (Using HTML, CSS, JavaScript)', 'During this time, I started by planning the game structure and layout for the Tic Tac Toe board. I created the basic HTML file with a 3x3 grid layout using <div> elements to represent the cells of the game board. I also planned how to handle user interactions such as clicking on a cell and alternating between player âXâ and player âOâ.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(959, '4196', '2025-10-24', '11AM-1PM', 'Meeting ( Registration and Login) Hitz Crafty', 'In this time meeting with Nanda sir and showing registration and login page of hitz crafty using springboot , thymeleaf, its mean full frontend and backend using my this project ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(960, '4194', '2025-10-24', '9AM-11AM', 'Project Presentation Preparation', 'Prepared for a meeting with the senior regarding ongoing projects.\r\n\r\nReviewed the Tic-Tac-Toe game project, ensuring all features in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript were working correctly.\r\n\r\nOrganized notes to explain the project logic, UI design, and code implementation clearly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(961, '4194', '2025-10-24', '11AM-1PM', 'Project Review â Tic-Tac-Toe Game', 'Attended a meeting with the senior and presented the Tic-Tac-Toe project.\r\n\r\nExplained the game features, including the UI, player turn logic, win/draw detection, and reset functionality.\r\n\r\nReceived feedback and suggestions for improvements.\r\n\r\nImplemented the suggested changes during the meeting itself, improving the functionality and user experience.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(962, '4194', '2025-10-24', '2PM-4PM', 'Project Presentation â Staff Management System', 'Presented the Staff Management System project:\r\n\r\nFrontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript\r\n\r\nBackend: Spring Boot\r\n\r\nImplemented CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)\r\n\r\nExplained the project architecture, functionality, and how the frontend communicates with the backend.\r\n\r\nReceived positive feedback and appreciation from the senior for the project implementation and UI design.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(963, '4194', '2025-10-24', '4PM-6PM', 'Project Feedback Implementation', 'Discussed and noted additional changes suggested by the senior for the Staff Management System.\r\n\r\nStarted implementing the changes and improvements during the meeting.\r\n\r\nEnsured all modifications are in line with the feedback and project standards.\r\n\r\nSenior praised the updated project functionality and gave approval to continue with the improvements.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(964, '4196', '2025-10-24', '2PM-4PM', 'Tic Tac Toe Game Development (Using HTML, CSS, JavaScript)', 'I worked on styling the board using CSS to make it visually appealing. I applied properties such as borders, alignment, spacing, and hover effects for each box. I also added a background color and font styling to clearly differentiate between player X and O moves. By the end of this time, the entire user interface for the game board was completed. and I focused on writing the JavaScript logic for the game This included tracking the turns, detecting player clicks, preventing overwriting of cells, and alternating between players correctly. I also implemented the logic to check for winning conditions â whether any player has three marks in a row, column, or diagonal.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
