(1021, '4194', '2025-10-29', '11AM-1PM', 'Advanced JavaScript Concepts', 'Explored callback functions and their role in managing asynchronous operations.\r\n\r\nImplemented examples of event handling and timed execution using callbacks.\r\n\r\nStudied Promises and their advantages over callbacks in simplifying async code.\r\n\r\nPracticed writing examples using .then() and .catch() for promise resolution and error handling.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1022, '4194', '2025-10-29', '2PM-4PM', 'Modern Asynchronous JavaScript', 'Learned about async and await keywords for cleaner asynchronous programming.\r\n\r\nCompared async/await with Promises to understand their relationship and benefits.\r\n\r\nConverted existing Promise-based code into async/await syntax to improve readability and maintainability.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1023, '4194', '2025-10-29', '4PM-6PM', 'API Integration in JavaScript', 'Studied the Fetch API for sending HTTP requests and handling responses.\r\n\r\nPracticed fetching and displaying data dynamically from a public API on a webpage.\r\n\r\nUnderstood error handling, response parsing (JSON format), and best practices for API integration.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1024, '4196', '2025-10-29', '4PM-6PM', 'Hitz Crafty Project â Backend Development in Spring Boot & Frontend Setup in VS Code', 'I shifted the frontend part of the project to VS Code for better interface design and development flexibility. I created the folder structure for HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files. The frontend was connected to the backend using REST APIs instead of Thymeleaf. I designed a simple, responsive UI using Bootstrap CSS and ensured that the frontend could successfully send and receive data from the backend.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1025, '4196', '2025-10-30', '9AM-11AM', 'Light On/Off application using (HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Bootstrap)', 'I began the day by planning and designing the basic structure of the Light On/Off project. Using HTML, I created a simple layout containing an image element for the bulb and two buttons â âTurn Onâ and âTurn Offâ. I structured the page to make it easy to handle through JavaScript later.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1026, '4196', '2025-10-30', '11AM-1PM', 'Light On/Off application using (HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Bootstrap)', 'In this session, I focused on styling the page using CSS and Bootstrap. I applied alignment, padding, and background color to make the interface visually appealing. Using Bootstrap classes, I made the buttons look more stylish and responsive, ensuring the layout adjusts properly across different screen sizes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1027, '4194', '2025-10-30', '9AM-11AM', 'Spring Boot â Pagination Concepts', 'Learned the concept of Pagination in Spring Boot.\r\n\r\nUnderstood why pagination is important for handling large datasets efficiently.\r\n\r\nStudied how pagination helps in improving application performance by retrieving limited records per request.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1028, '4194', '2025-10-30', '11AM-1PM', 'Spring Boot â Pagination Implementation', 'Implemented Pagination using Spring Boot and JPA Repository.\r\n\r\nLearned about key classes and interfaces like Page, Pageable, and PageRequest.\r\n\r\nPracticed how to set page number, size, and sorting order to display records dynamically.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1029, '4194', '2025-10-30', '2PM-4PM', 'Spring Boot â CRUD Operations', 'Integrated pagination feature within the existing project to enhance data management and UI display.\r\n\r\nWorked on API testing and validation for pagination endpoints.\r\n\r\nDebugged minor issues and ensured the pagination and CRUD operations were working seamlessly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1030, '4194', '2025-10-30', '4PM-6PM', 'Spring Boot â CRUD Operations', 'Revised and implemented CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) in Spring Boot.\r\n\r\nIntegrated pagination logic into CRUD endpoints to fetch paginated data.\r\n\r\nTested APIs using Postman to verify pagination and CRUD functionalities.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1031, '3697', '2025-10-30', '9AM-11AM', 'Spring Framework Learning', 'Studied the core concepts of Spring Boot, including project structure, auto-configuration, and dependency management. Explored how to create and run a Spring Boot application using SpringApplication.run(). Learned about annotations like @SpringBootApplication, @RestController, and @RequestMapping.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yandra Ravi Babu'),
(1032, '3697', '2025-10-30', '11AM-1PM', 'Spring Framework Learning', 'Studied the core concepts of Spring Boot, including project structure, auto-configuration, and dependency management. Explored how to create and run a Spring Boot application using SpringApplication.run(). Learned about annotations like @SpringBootApplication, @RestController, and @RequestMapping.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yandra Ravi Babu'),
(1033, '3697', '2025-10-30', '2PM-4PM', 'Spring Framework Learning', 'Studied the core concepts of Spring Boot, including project structure, auto-configuration, and dependency management. Explored how to create and run a Spring Boot application using SpringApplication.run(). Learned about annotations like @SpringBootApplication, @RestController, and @RequestMapping.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yandra Ravi Babu'),
(1034, '4196', '2025-10-30', '2PM-4PM', 'Light On/Off application using (HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Bootstrap)', 'I wrote the JavaScript logic for turning the light bulb image on and off. I used the onclick event to change the image source dynamically â one image for the bulb switched on and another for off. I also added console logs for debugging and tested the event triggers to confirm the logic worked smoothly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
