(1043, '4196', '2025-10-31', '9AM-11AM', 'Hitz Crafty Project â Email Integration After User Registration', 'I began the day by planning and setting up the email feature for the Hitz Crafty application. I reviewed the existing registration module to understand the flow of user data and identified where to trigger the email after successful registration. I also added the Spring Boot Mail dependency in the projectâs pom.xml file to enable email-sending functionality.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1044, '4196', '2025-10-31', '11AM-1PM', 'Hitz Crafty Project â Email Integration After User Registration', 'I worked on configuring the email settings inside the application.properties file. I added the necessary SMTP configurations such as host, port, username, and password for sending emails. I then created a MailService class responsible for building and sending welcome emails to newly registered users.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1045, '4196', '2025-10-31', '2PM-4PM', 'Hitz Crafty Project â Email Integration After User Registration', 'I integrated the MailService with the User Registration Controller. Once a user successfully registers, the application now triggers an automatic email to the userâs provided email address. The email contains a personalized welcome message â âWelcome to Hitz Crafty!â â confirming successful registration. I also added exception handling to ensure smooth operation even if the mail server faces temporary issues.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1046, '4196', '2025-10-31', '4PM-6PM', 'Hitz Crafty Project â Email Integration After User Registration', 'I tested the entire registration and email flow. After registering multiple users, I verified that each one received a proper welcome email in their inbox. I refined the email content and subject line, giving it a friendly and professional tone. Finally, I reviewed the overall functionality to ensure the feature works seamlessly along with the existing registration system.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
