(1051, '4194', '2025-10-31', '9AM-11AM', 'JavaScript Fundamentals â Object-Oriented Programming', 'Studied the concept of Classes and Objects in JavaScript. Learned how to define classes, create object instances, and use constructors and methods effectively. Practiced multiple coding examples to understand object behavior, encapsulation, and code reusability.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1052, '4194', '2025-10-31', '11AM-1PM', 'Advanced JavaScript Concepts', 'Explored callback functions and their role in managing asynchronous operations. Implemented examples of event handling and timed execution using callbacks. Studied Promises and their advantages over callbacks in simplifying async code. Practiced writing examples using .then() and .catch() for promise resolution and error handling.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
