(1067, '4196', '2025-11-03', '9AM-11AM', 'Hitz Crafty Project â Email Verification Setup Using Brevo', 'I began the day by researching and understanding the Brevo (Sendinblue) email service for integration with the Hitz Crafty project. I created an account on the Brevo platform and explored its SMTP and API options for sending verification emails. I also reviewed the existing registration workflow to decide the best point to trigger the email verification process after user signup.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1068, '4196', '2025-11-03', '11AM-1PM', 'Hitz Crafty Project â Email Verification Setup Using Brevo', 'During this time, I configured Brevoâs SMTP settings in the application.properties file of my Spring Boot project. I added the Brevo SMTP host, port, username (API key), and password for secure authentication. Once configured, I tested a sample email to confirm successful communication between my Spring Boot app and Brevoâs mail server.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1069, '4196', '2025-11-03', '2PM-4PM', 'Hitz Crafty Project â Email Verification Setup Using Brevo', 'I focused on implementing the email verification feature. I updated the registration controller so that whenever a new user registers, a verification link is generated and sent to their registered email ID. The link contains a unique token that confirms the userâs email when clicked. I also created a verification endpoint to validate the token and update the userâs status to âverifiedâ in the database.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
