(1081, '4139', '2025-11-04', '9AM-11AM', 'LinkedIn Post', 'A total of eight (8) LinkedIn posts** have been published across two official company pages.\r\nThese posts primarily focused on promoting Salesforce Marketing Cloud (SFMC) and Salesforce Data Cloud career opportunities, training programs, and industry insights.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Subhajit Ghosh'),
(1082, '4196', '2025-11-04', '9AM-11AM', 'Hitz Crafty Project â Add to Cart Functionality Implementation', 'I began the day by planning the Add to Cart feature and reviewing the existing product display section of the Hitz Crafty application. I analyzed how product data was being fetched from the database and decided how to store selected products when users click on âAdd to Cart.â I created a Cart entity class in the backend to represent items that users add to their shopping cart.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1083, '4196', '2025-11-04', '11AM-1PM', 'Hitz Crafty Project â Add to Cart Functionality Implementation', 'I focused on setting up the repository and service layers for the Cart module. The repository handled database operations like saving and fetching cart items, while the service layer managed the business logic such as adding items, updating quantities, and removing products from the cart. I also created REST API endpoints in the controller for cart operations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1084, '4196', '2025-11-04', '2PM-4PM', 'Hitz Crafty Project â Add to Cart Functionality Implementation', 'I worked on integrating the Add to Cart functionality with the frontend. Using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Bootstrap, I added an âAdd to Cartâ button under each product. When clicked, the product details are sent to the backend through an API call and stored in the userâs cart. I also displayed a success message after each addition and tested the API connections using Postman and browser console logs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
