(1105, '4196', '2025-11-05', '2PM-4PM', 'Rock Paper Scissors Game Development', 'I implemented the JavaScript game logic. I wrote functions to randomly generate the computerâs choice, compare it with the userâs choice, and determine the winner based on standard game rules (Rock beats Scissors, Paper beats Rock, Scissors beats Paper). I also updated the DOM dynamically to show results and track scores for both the player and the computer.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1106, '4073', '2025-11-05', '4PM-6PM', 'Java methods are reusable blocks of code that perform specific tasks and help organize your program', 'Java methods are reusable blocks of code that perform specific tasks and help organize your program', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SHANMUKH ASAI SASTRY KALAJULAPATI '),
(1107, '4196', '2025-11-05', '4PM-6PM', 'Rock Paper Scissors Game Development', 'I focused on testing and improving the game experience. I fixed minor bugs in result display and score updates, added a reset button, and made sure the game flow worked smoothly for multiple rounds. I also enhanced the interface by showing emojis and color feedback â green for win, red for loss, and gray for draw â to make the game more interactive and fun.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1108, '4194', '2025-11-05', '9AM-11AM', 'JavaScript Fundamentals â Object-Oriented Programming', 'Studied the concept of Classes and Objects in JavaScript.\r\n\r\nLearned how to define classes, create object instances, and effectively use constructors and methods.\r\n\r\nPracticed multiple coding examples to understand object behavior, encapsulation, and code reusability.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1109, '4194', '2025-11-05', '11AM-1PM', 'Advanced JavaScript Concepts', 'Explored callback functions and their role in handling asynchronous operations.\r\n\r\nImplemented event handling and timed execution using callbacks.\r\n\r\nStudied Promises and their advantages over callbacks for simplifying async code.\r\n\r\nPracticed writing examples using .then() and .catch() for promise resolution and error handling.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1110, '4194', '2025-11-05', '2PM-4PM', 'Modern Asynchronous JavaScript', 'Learned about async and await keywords for cleaner asynchronous programming.\r\n\r\nCompared async/await with Promises to understand their relationship and benefits.\r\n\r\nConverted existing Promise-based code into async/await syntax to enhance readability and maintainability.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1111, '4194', '2025-11-05', '4PM-6PM', 'API Integration in JavaScript', 'Studied the Fetch API for sending HTTP requests and handling responses.\r\n\r\nPracticed fetching and displaying data dynamically from a public API on a webpage.\r\n\r\nUnderstood error handling, response parsing (JSON format), and best practices for API integration.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1112, '4196', '2025-11-06', '9AM-11AM', 'Introduction to React.js', 'I began with an introduction to React.js, learning about its purpose, features, and advantages over traditional JavaScript. I understood concepts like component-based architecture, virtual DOM, and one-way data binding. I also explored how React improves performance and reusability in modern web applications.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1113, '4196', '2025-11-06', '11AM-1PM', 'Introduction to React.js', ', I set up the React development environment. I installed Node.js, npm, and created my first React app using the create-react-app command. I explored the folder structure (src, public, node_modules) and understood the role of important files like index.js, App.js, and package.json.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1114, '4196', '2025-11-06', '2PM-4PM', 'Introduction to React.js', 'I started learning JSX (JavaScript XML) and how it combines HTML with JavaScript inside React components. I practiced writing simple functional components and rendering them on the browser. I also learned about the importance of ReactDOM.render() and how components are connected in a React app.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1115, '4073', '2025-11-06', '9AM-11AM', 'Java is an object oriented language and some concepts may be new', 'Java is an object oriented language and some concepts may be new', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SHANMUKH ASAI SASTRY KALAJULAPATI '),
(1116, '4073', '2025-11-06', '11AM-1PM', 'the return type of the method. It means it does not return any value', 'the return type of the method. It means it does not return any value', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SHANMUKH ASAI SASTRY KALAJULAPATI '),
(1117, '4073', '2025-11-06', '2PM-4PM', 'We will learn about var-args later in the Java New Features chapter', 'We will learn about var-args later in the Java New Features chapter', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SHANMUKH ASAI SASTRY KALAJULAPATI '),
(1118, '4073', '2025-11-06', '4PM-6PM', 'This class is used for reading and writing to random access file', 'This class is used for reading and writing to random access file', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SHANMUKH ASAI SASTRY KALAJULAPATI '),
(1119, '4196', '2025-11-06', '4PM-6PM', 'Introduction to React.js', 'I created a small demo project â âHello React Appâ â to test my understanding. I customized components, passed props, and applied inline CSS styling. I also learned how to use export/import for organizing multiple components in a project.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1120, '4194', '2025-11-06', '9AM-11AM', 'Project Setup & Create API Implementation', 'Set up a new Spring Boot project using Spring Initializr\r\n\r\nAdded dependencies:\r\n\r\nspring-boot-starter-web\r\n\r\nspring-boot-starter-data-jpa\r\n\r\nmysql-connector-j\r\n\r\nConfigured application.properties for PostgreSQLdatabase connection', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1121, '4194', '2025-11-06', '11AM-1PM', 'Project Setup & Create API Implementation', 'Created:\r\n\r\nVenueEntity (Entity class with fields like id, name, location, capacity, etc.)\r\n\r\nVenueRepository (extends JpaRepository<VenueEntity, Long>)\r\n\r\nImplemented Create (POST) API to insert new venue records into the database\r\n\r\nTested API successfully in Postman', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1122, '4194', '2025-11-06', '2PM-4PM', 'Spring Boot CRUD Operations â Read API', 'Implemented Read (GET) APIs:\r\n\r\nGET /venues ? Fetch all venue records\r\n\r\nGET /venues/{id} ? Fetch specific record by ID\r\n\r\nAdded Service layer for better architecture:\r\n\r\nController ? Service ? Repository pattern\r\n\r\nImplemented custom exception handling for âRecord Not Foundâ\r\n\r\nVerified all endpoints using Postman', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1123, '4194', '2025-11-06', '4PM-6PM', 'Spring Boot CRUD Operations â Update API', 'Implemented Update (PUT) API to modify existing records\r\n\r\nUsed @PathVariable for ID and @RequestBody for updated data\r\n\r\nAdded input validations using annotations like @NotNull, @Size, etc.\r\n\r\nTested with various input cases and validated proper error responses', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1124, '4139', '2025-11-06', '9AM-11AM', 'LinkedIn Post', 'Post Data Cloude Master Session post in Linkedin', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Subhajit Ghosh'),
(1125, '4196', '2025-11-07', '9AM-11AM', 'React â State, Props, and Hooks', 'I will start the day by revising React components and understanding the difference between functional and class components. Then, Iâll focus on props (properties) â how to pass data from one component to another, how props are immutable, and how they help in dynamic rendering of UI content.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1126, '4196', '2025-11-07', '11AM-1PM', 'React â State, Props, and Hooks', 'Next, Iâll learn about React state management. Iâll explore how to create and update state using the useState() hook in functional components. Iâll build small examples like a counter app and toggle button to understand how state changes trigger re-rendering in React.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1127, '4196', '2025-11-07', '2PM-4PM', 'React â State, Props, and Hooks', 'In this session, Iâll study React Hooks in more detail â mainly useEffect() and how it handles side effects such as API calls or data fetching. Iâll practice examples that use both useState() and useEffect() together to manage and update component behavior dynamically.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1128, '4196', '2025-11-07', '4PM-6PM', 'React â State, Props, and Hooks', 'Finally, Iâll work on a mini React project that combines all the learned concepts â props, state, and hooks. For example, a live clock app or task tracker where data updates in real-time. Iâll also add some basic styling using Bootstrap and CSS modules to make the UI neat and interactive.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
