(1160, '4073', '2025-11-11', '2PM-4PM', 'package are used to perform io related operations', 'package are used to perform io related operations', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SHANMUKH ASAI SASTRY KALAJULAPATI '),
(1161, '4073', '2025-11-11', '4PM-6PM', 'Marker interface can be defined as the interface ', 'Marker interface can be defined as the interface ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SHANMUKH ASAI SASTRY KALAJULAPATI '),
(1162, '4196', '2025-11-11', '4PM-6PM', 'To-Do List Application Development (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)', 'Finally, I enhanced the app by adding delete functionality for each task and local storage support to save tasks even after page reload. I tested the app for various scenarios â adding, marking complete, deleting, and refreshing â to ensure everything worked smoothly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1163, '4194', '2025-11-11', '9AM-11AM', 'Spring Boot CRUD Operations â Project Setup & Create Operation', 'Set up a new Spring Boot project using Spring Initializr.\r\n\r\nAdded dependencies:\r\n\r\nspring-boot-starter-web\r\n\r\nspring-boot-starter-data-jpa\r\n\r\nmysql-connector-j\r\n\r\nConfigured application.properties for MySQL database connection.\r\n\r\nCreated:\r\n\r\nEntity class: VenueEntity\r\n\r\nRepository interface\r\n\r\nImplemented the Create (POST) API to insert data into the database.\r\n\r\nSuccessfully tested the Create API using Postman.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1164, '4194', '2025-11-11', '11AM-1PM', 'Read Operation', 'Implemented Read (GET) APIs:\r\n\r\nGET /entities ? Fetch all records\r\n\r\nGET /entities/{id} ? Fetch record by ID\r\n\r\nAdded a Service Layer for proper architecture (Controller ? Service ? Repository).\r\n\r\nTested both endpoints using Postman.\r\n\r\nImplemented custom exception handling for ârecord not foundâ scenarios.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1165, '4194', '2025-11-11', '2PM-4PM', 'Update Operation', 'Implemented the Update (PUT) API to modify existing records.\r\n\r\nUsed @PathVariable and @RequestBody correctly for data mapping.\r\n\r\nAdded input validation annotations such as @NotNull and @Size.\r\n\r\nTested API with multiple inputs and handled error conditions effectively.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1166, '4194', '2025-11-11', '4PM-6PM', 'Delete Operation & Final Testing', 'Implemented the Delete (DELETE) API to remove records by ID.\r\n\r\nAdded a validation check for non-existing IDs.\r\n\r\nPerformed full CRUD cycle testing in Postman (Create ? Read ? Update ? Delete).\r\n\r\nCompleted code cleanup, documentation, and committed the final version to GitHub.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1167, '4196', '2025-11-12', '9AM-11AM', 'Counter Application (Increase & Decrease Counting)', 'I started by designing the basic HTML structure for the counter application. It included a display area to show the current count value and three buttons â Increase, Decrease, and Reset. I used simple and clean HTML elements like div, h1, and button to build the structure.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1168, '4196', '2025-11-12', '11AM-1PM', 'Counter Application (Increase & Decrease Counting)', 'Next, I focused on styling the interface using CSS. I centered the counter on the screen using Flexbox, added padding, borders, and color effects for the buttons. I also applied hover effects and different colors for each button â green for increase, red for decrease, and blue for reset â to improve the user experience.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1169, '4196', '2025-11-12', '2PM-4PM', 'Counter Application (Increase & Decrease Counting)', ' I implemented the JavaScript functionality. I created variables to track the count and wrote event listeners for all three buttons. Clicking âIncreaseâ increments the count, âDecreaseâ decrements it (without going below zero if restricted), and âResetâ brings it back to zero. The displayed value updates instantly on the screen.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1170, '3697', '2025-11-12', '9AM-11AM', 'Learning the concepts of Spring Boot', 'Studied the working of Spring Boot annotations and dependency injection.\r\n\r\nPracticed creating RESTful APIs using Spring Boot.\r\n\r\nUnderstood how to connect Spring Boot applications with MySQL database using JPA.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yandra Ravi Babu'),
(1171, '3697', '2025-11-12', '11AM-1PM', 'Practical Implementation', 'Created a Student entity and implemented CRUD operations.\r\n\r\nDebugged getter method issues in the entity class.\r\n\r\nIntegrated Thymeleaf templates to display student details.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yandra Ravi Babu'),
(1172, '3697', '2025-11-12', '2PM-4PM', 'Revision and Testing', 'Tested all CRUD functionalities using Postman.\r\n\r\nVerified data persistence in the MySQL database.\r\n\r\nRevised Spring Boot concepts and reviewed project structure.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yandra Ravi Babu'),
(1173, '4073', '2025-11-12', '9AM-11AM', '	Returns the pathname string of the parent directory', '	Returns the pathname string of the parent directory', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SHANMUKH ASAI SASTRY KALAJULAPATI '),
(1174, '4073', '2025-11-12', '11AM-1PM', ' SQL is a standard language for storing, manipulating and retrieving data in database', '\r\nSQL is a standard language for storing, manipulating and retrieving data in database', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SHANMUKH ASAI SASTRY KALAJULAPATI '),
(1175, '4073', '2025-11-12', '2PM-4PM', 'this tutorial end with an exercise where you can check your level of knowledge', 'this tutorial end with an exercise where you can check your level of knowledge', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SHANMUKH ASAI SASTRY KALAJULAPATI '),
(1176, '4073', '2025-11-12', '4PM-6PM', 'A table is a collection of related data entries and it consists of columns and rows', 'A table is a collection of related data entries and it consists of columns and rows', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SHANMUKH ASAI SASTRY KALAJULAPATI '),
(1177, '4196', '2025-11-12', '4PM-6PM', 'Counter Application (Increase & Decrease Counting)', 'Finally, I enhanced the app with small improvements â such as changing the text color dynamically based on the count (green when positive, red when negative, black when zero). I also tested the application thoroughly to ensure smooth button clicks and accurate updates on different browsers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1178, '4194', '2025-11-12', '9AM-11AM', 'Project Discussion', 'Had a meeting with the senior to discuss the ongoing project, including progress updates and next development steps.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1179, '4194', '2025-11-12', '11AM-1PM', 'Learning â Web Technologies', 'Studied the differences between JSP, Servlet, and Spring Boot, understanding their architecture, use cases, and advantages of Spring Boot over traditional Java web technologies.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1180, '4194', '2025-11-12', '2PM-4PM', 'Spring Boot Development', 'Started learning Spring Boot. Created project structure with packages â DTO, Service, Entity, Repository, and Controller. Implemented initial setup for CRUD operations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1181, '4194', '2025-11-12', '4PM-6PM', 'Coding & Implementation', 'Implemented two methods â getAllDetails() and getById() â in the service and controller layers. Currently working on developing another method to extend functionality.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Muskan'),
(1182, '2789', '2025-11-12', '9AM-11AM', 'Project and training department ', 'Working on personal project ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2789'),
(1183, '4196', '2025-11-13', '9AM-11AM', 'Zomato Portal (Frontend Design & Functionality)', 'I began by designing the basic structure of the Zomato Portal using HTML. The layout included a navigation bar with the Zomato logo, menu links (Home, Explore, Login, Signup), and a search section for restaurants. I also created sections for featured restaurants and offers to give it a real-world Zomato-like look.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1184, '4196', '2025-11-13', '11AM-1PM', 'Zomato Portal (Frontend Design & Functionality)', 'Next, I focused on styling the webpage using CSS. I applied a modern, food-themed color palette (red, white, and black), added hover effects on menu links, styled the search bar, and made the restaurant cards visually appealing using box shadows and border-radius. I also ensured the design was responsive using Flexbox and media queries', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
(1185, '4196', '2025-11-13', '2PM-4PM', 'Zomato Portal (Frontend Design & Functionality)', 'In this session, I added JavaScript functionality to make the page interactive. I implemented dynamic search behavior where users can type restaurant names, and the suggestions update accordingly. I also added basic animations and smooth scrolling effects to enhance the user experience.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jayshree'),
